{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "By using prompting or ICL strategies, the related knowledge will be extracted out in different text forms to facilitate recommendation tasks [25,145,159].",
    "One form of auxiliary textual information is summarization or text generation, enabling LLMs to enrich representations of users or items [148].",
    "For example, Du et al. [25] proposed a job recommendation model which utilized the capability of LLMs for summarization to extract user information and job requirements.",
    "Mysore et al. [96], on the other hand, used the ICL strategy to instruct LLMs for narrative queries according to the interaction history of users, which was then utilized as the source data for training narrative driver recommendation models.",
    "Considering item descriptions and user reviews, KAR [159] extracted the reasoning knowledge on user preferences and the factual knowledge on items through specifically designed prompts, while SAGCN [84] utilized a chain-based prompting strategy to generate semantic information."
  ],
